snippet: Voters in Serbia expressed their anger with the governing party, and Ivica Dacic, a former spokesman for Slobodan Milosevic, indicated that being made prime minister was the price of his support.
abstract: Serbian voters appear to have denied a clear mandate to either of country's two leading parties in an election colored by anger and disillusionment over high unemployment; early election results seem to give the Socialists, party once led by Slobodan Milosevic, an opportunity to play kingmaker.
lead_paragraph: Voters in Serbia expressed their anger with the governing party, and Ivica Dacic, a former spokesman for Slobodan Milosevic, indicated that being made prime minister was the price of his support.

headline.seo: Milosevic Party Emerges as Kingmaker in Serbia
headline.print_headline: Party of Milosevic Emerges As Kingmaker in Serbian Vote
